(33095, 'tiagabine hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Carbamazepine, phenytoin, primidone, and phenobarbital are generally classified as enzyme inducers; valproate and gabapentin are not.', 'DailyMed'),
(33095, 'pregabalin', 'N/A', 'minor', 'No pharmacokinetic interactions were observed between pregabalin and carbamazepine, gabapentin, lamotrigine, oral contraceptive, phenobarbital, phenytoin, topiramate, and valproic acid.', 'DailyMed'),
